01:19:39.880 --> 01:19:47.880
[Guest]: board painting interestingly is the first kind of ad agency job in a way post-independence

01:19:47.880 --> 01:19:56.880
[Guest]: India at that time if you see you had to do local advertising you were not even given

01:19:56.880 --> 01:20:00.880
[Guest]: graphics sometimes someone used to come and say we have a sweet shop and we have to do

01:20:00.880 --> 01:20:05.880
[Guest]: this kind of thing so you are an artist you are creating you are basically doing everything

01:20:05.880 --> 01:20:17.880
[Guest]: the departments of an ad agency from client servicing to creative director to copywriter

01:20:17.880 --> 01:20:22.880
[Guest]: to graphics you do all the work so they were doing it at that time right after independence

01:20:22.880 --> 01:20:28.880
[Guest]: they moved from Pakistan to this place in Haryana called Jagadri which is now Yamuna Nagar and

01:20:28.880 --> 01:20:35.880
[Guest]: Jagadri if there are two districts next to each other, so at that time he was in Yamuna

01:20:35.880 --> 01:20:41.880
[Guest]: Nagar but it was a part of the Jagadri district, Yamuna Nagar was a town and they moved from

01:20:41.880 --> 01:20:48.880
[Guest]: Lyalpur in Pakistan post partition Punjabi family so this was going on on my father's

01:20:48.880 --> 01:20:55.880
[Guest]: side where my father saw painting from childhood and my father has also learned painting a

01:20:55.880 --> 01:21:02.880
[Guest]: lot from my father and while doing that the work of making film posters also started coming

01:21:02.880 --> 01:21:09.880
[Guest]: to him because a local theater was opened single screen so because of film posters three

01:21:09.880 --> 01:21:15.880
[Guest]: brothers got interested in films so my father was always a big fan of cinema right from

01:21:15.880 --> 01:21:21.880
[Guest]: probably he was 12 or something when his two elder brothers were handling the work of painting

01:21:21.880 --> 01:21:31.880
[Guest]: and because he was the youngest, it was decided in the house that let him study, work is going

01:21:31.880 --> 01:21:38.880
[Guest]: on, business whatever is going on, family business, so my father was sent to college

01:21:38.880 --> 01:21:46.880
[Guest]: school, he used to study well, went to college, did his diploma in engineering from Chandigarh

01:21:46.880 --> 01:21:53.880
[Guest]: Punjab University which later I think became Punjab Engineering College from where he did

01:21:53.880 --> 01:21:59.880
[Guest]: diploma which was later, because at that time diploma was only there in 50s or 60s, B.Tech

01:21:59.880 --> 01:22:06.880
[Guest]: was not that much, so later it was considered equivalent to B.Tech so he is kind of, he

01:22:06.880 --> 01:22:12.880
[Guest]: is an engineer in mechanical, I think production was, it was called production engineering

01:22:12.880 --> 01:22:19.880
[Guest]: at that time, so from there he worked in 2-3 places in press and in many places where there

01:22:19.880 --> 01:22:25.880
[Guest]: was machinery, he worked there, after that he got a job in Himachal, there was a place

01:22:25.880 --> 01:22:32.880
[Guest]: called Sundarnagar where we used to live, but that job was in Salapad, Salapad Mandi

01:22:32.880 --> 01:22:40.880
[Guest]: which is the district of Himachal, there was this hydel electric plant being made which

01:22:40.880 --> 01:22:49.880
[Guest]: I think was Himachal's first dam project, this was late 70s, and there he got a job

01:22:49.880 --> 01:22:57.880
[Guest]: as junior engineer, so he was there, then he got married to my mom and I was born there

01:22:57.880 --> 01:23:05.880
[Guest]: in 1980, so from childhood at home, because papa was very fond of films, still is, he

01:23:05.880 --> 01:23:11.880
[Guest]: knows more gossips than me, still he shows many things, his trailer has come, I didn't

01:23:11.880 --> 01:23:20.880
[Guest]: know that, his trailer has come, generally I am very clued in, I am still a very pop

01:23:20.880 --> 01:23:29.880
[Guest]: culture enthusiast, so childhood, we lived in Sundarnagar for 6 years, then from there

01:23:29.880 --> 01:23:35.880
[Guest]: the dam project was completed, then he got posting into military engineering services,

01:23:35.880 --> 01:23:40.880
[Guest]: so we came to Dehradun, so I remember the first 6 years very vaguely, I just remember

01:23:40.880 --> 01:23:44.880
[Guest]: that we were in Sundarnagar, there was only one theatre, we used to go there to watch

01:23:44.880 --> 01:23:48.880
[Guest]: films, and I remember the first film also, we watched Nikah, I mean I remember it in

01:23:48.880 --> 01:23:53.880
[Guest]: my memory, maybe I have seen it before, but I remember Nikah and Masoom, there were two

01:23:53.880 --> 01:24:02.880
[Guest]: films that we had seen in theatre at that time, and then from childhood, not only films,

01:24:02.880 --> 01:24:12.880
[Guest]: but also music, books, my father is a big reader, he is very fond of reading, since

01:24:12.880 --> 01:24:17.880
[Guest]: childhood I have seen that he used to come home in the evening and pick up a book or

01:24:17.880 --> 01:24:23.880
[Guest]: a newspaper, he used to read newspaper a lot, I mean he has a habit of reading newspapers,

01:24:23.880 --> 01:24:28.880
[Guest]: till now it is Sunday, so on Sunday he will bring 3-4 newspapers and then he will read

01:24:28.880 --> 01:24:36.880
[Guest]: it for the next 3-4 days, so because of that, I got a lot of books at home since childhood,

01:24:36.880 --> 01:24:41.880
[Guest]: and the specific books for children that used to come at that time, there was Parag, there

01:24:41.880 --> 01:24:48.880
[Guest]: was Nandan, there was Baal Hans, which was probably the most literary of all the magazines

01:24:48.880 --> 01:24:59.880
[Guest]: for children at that time, because Champak and Nandan, and Chanda Mama, and Suman Saurabh,

01:24:59.880 --> 01:25:07.880
[Guest]: and Nanna Samrat, these were all typical Disney ideas of children, that children are cute

01:25:07.880 --> 01:25:13.880
[Guest]: and they want cute stories, or they want interesting stories, or they want mythological stories,

01:25:13.880 --> 01:25:19.880
[Guest]: I don't know who had put this idea at that time, which is still there in India, I think

01:25:19.880 --> 01:25:27.880
[Guest]: Chota Bheem is one of the most popular animation series, but there were a lot of books, and

01:25:27.880 --> 01:25:33.880
[Guest]: in that Baal Hans was a little more mature, there was a little more scientific temperament

01:25:33.880 --> 01:25:42.880
[Guest]: and the stories were not so cute and simplistic, so all these books, I think I remember from

01:25:42.880 --> 01:25:47.880
[Guest]: childhood, from the time I started reading, I mean from the age of 4-5 years, when you

01:25:47.880 --> 01:25:54.880
[Guest]: add words and sentences from A-B-C-D and make a sentence and read it, since then I have

01:25:54.880 --> 01:26:05.880
[Guest]: been fond of reading, and maybe because I got the material to read, so from Himachal

01:26:05.880 --> 01:26:11.880
[Guest]: we came to Dehradun, we came to Dehradun, where actually I started reading probably

01:26:11.880 --> 01:26:17.880
[Guest]: more seriously, because from the age of 7 to the age of 12, I stayed in Dehradun,

01:26:17.880 --> 01:26:31.880
[Guest]: from 1986 to 1992, and during that time I got fond of writing, not just reading, because

01:26:31.880 --> 01:26:38.880
[Guest]: I think everyone learns like that, I don't know, I think so, but if you read a lot,

01:26:38.880 --> 01:26:47.880
[Guest]: then you want to show off that I read this, and there are 2-3 ways to show off, either

01:26:47.880 --> 01:26:54.880
[Guest]: you tell someone that I read this, or you write and confirm that I have learned a new

01:26:54.880 --> 01:27:02.880
[Guest]: word and I will write it now, so in your usage, you kind of make it your own, with your own

01:27:02.880 --> 01:27:10.880
[Guest]: usage, so I started doing such things at the same time, at the age of 8-9 years, I kept

01:27:10.880 --> 01:27:17.880
[Guest]: writing something small, because there were so many books and magazines, and stories

01:27:17.880 --> 01:27:23.880
[Guest]: were seen in them, so it was understood that someone is writing, and writing is a cool

01:27:23.880 --> 01:27:32.880
[Guest]: thing, it was in my mind since then, that the people who write, they are such great people

01:27:32.880 --> 01:27:41.880
[Guest]: that we wait for a new edition every month, it was a very exciting time, 4-5 days in the

01:27:41.880 --> 01:27:48.880
[Guest]: beginning of the month, when it used to come, when all the magazines, their monthly edition

01:27:48.880 --> 01:27:55.880
[Guest]: used to come to a nearby book store, and we used to go there and pick it, it was a very

01:27:55.880 --> 01:28:04.880
[Guest]: exciting time and it was something which developed in me an idea that this is a very valuable

01:28:04.880 --> 01:28:12.880
[Guest]: thing, this thrill, this adventure of turning a page and reading and discovering a new story

01:28:12.880 --> 01:28:21.880
[Guest]: at the same time, it is a very good association, generally the memory association, because

01:28:21.880 --> 01:28:26.880
[Guest]: of which our whole life, I mean, there are many things that become a bad association,

01:28:26.880 --> 01:28:30.880
[Guest]: because of which you are not able to learn swimming all your life, sometimes or sometimes

01:28:30.880 --> 01:28:35.880
[Guest]: you are not able to go to a particular place, so for me that association is very beautiful

01:28:35.880 --> 01:28:42.880
[Guest]: since then, and then at the age of 10, I wrote a story, because there was a story in Balhans,

01:28:42.880 --> 01:28:50.880
[Guest]: Chuchu went away, or Chuchu went away, something like that was his name, it was about a child

01:28:50.880 --> 01:28:56.880
[Guest]: who gets a baby bird, injured on the road, and he takes care of it for a few days, a good

01:28:56.880 --> 01:29:00.880
[Guest]: relationship is formed between the two, and finally when the baby bird recovers, it flies

01:29:00.880 --> 01:29:07.880
[Guest]: away, so this story ends here, now for a 10-year-old child, it was a very tragic tale, and generally

01:29:07.880 --> 01:29:13.880
[Guest]: what, why I am saying, and why I was saying that Balhans was different from other books

01:29:13.880 --> 01:29:20.880
[Guest]: that it had a sad ending story like this, which I think Champak or any other magazine

01:29:20.880 --> 01:29:26.880
[Guest]: would never dare, that in a book of small children, there is a story with a sad kind

01:29:26.880 --> 01:29:33.880
[Guest]: of an ending, you develop a beautiful relationship and then the bird flies away, so I was worried

01:29:33.880 --> 01:29:42.880
[Guest]: for many days after reading that story, and I felt very bad that why this relationship

01:29:42.880 --> 01:29:50.880
[Guest]: did not continue, such a good relationship of a child and a bird, and then I, one day

01:29:50.880 --> 01:29:58.880
[Guest]: I had a fever, so I did not go to school, and my mother also used to teach in a school,

01:29:58.880 --> 01:30:03.880
[Guest]: so she went to school, my father also went to school, my younger brother also went to

01:30:03.880 --> 01:30:08.880
[Guest]: school, I was alone at home, they gave me medicine, it was the days of winters in the

01:30:08.880 --> 01:30:15.880
[Guest]: sun, outside in the sun, folding, a nylon bed used to come, they sat on it and left,

01:30:15.880 --> 01:30:20.880
[Guest]: I was sitting, then I felt that something should be done about this story, I am not

01:30:20.880 --> 01:30:28.880
[Guest]: going to take it lying down, so I wrote a sequel to that story, in which after a few

01:30:28.880 --> 01:30:33.880
[Guest]: years, the same bird was found again and then a relationship was formed between the two

01:30:33.880 --> 01:30:39.880
[Guest]: and this time it was a more, whatever in my ideal world, it was like, okay, we won't

01:30:39.880 --> 01:30:45.880
[Guest]: cage the bird, but the bird will come back on its own every day just to say hello, so

01:30:45.880 --> 01:30:51.880
[Guest]: the bird is free, but it keeps coming to that boy every day, so I wrote something like this

01:30:51.880 --> 01:30:58.880
[Guest]: and then my parents read that thing and they said that it is good, we can send it, let's

01:30:58.880 --> 01:31:05.880
[Guest]: see what happens, and we sent it to Balhant and Balhant published it, and that was kind

01:31:05.880 --> 01:31:11.880
[Guest]: of a major confidence booster, at the age of 10, you write something for a magazine,

01:31:11.880 --> 01:31:17.880
[Guest]: you are completely in love with, and they published it and they also sent 50 rupees

01:31:17.880 --> 01:31:26.880
[Guest]: ka Parishramik, jo uss samay mila 50 rupee, jo bahut badi rakam thi, 1990 mein 50 rupee,

01:31:26.880 --> 01:31:32.880
[Guest]: matlab wo bhi uss samay, we are talking about pre Narsimha Rao, pre Manmohan Singh time,

01:31:32.880 --> 01:31:37.880
[Guest]: Indian economy was really going through a bad time, 50 rupee ek bachche ko aapne de

01:31:37.880 --> 01:31:47.880
[Guest]: diye the, toh mera pehli kamayi bhi thi zindagi ki, and it kind of, that, I believe it kind

01:31:47.880 --> 01:31:53.880
[Guest]: of opened a door that, that was the first time I thought, okay, I'll be a writer someday,

01:31:53.880 --> 01:31:58.880
[Guest]: ki paise bhi milte hain, chhapta bhi hain, aur aap kuch karte hain, aur uski tarif bhi

01:31:58.880 --> 01:32:07.880
[Guest]: karte hai, aur toh waha se phir mene seriously, seriously matlab uss aim ke saath ki chhapana

01:32:07.880 --> 01:32:12.880
[Guest]: hai, chhapna chahiye, uss tarah se likhna hai, toh agle kuch saalon mein phir aur kuch

01:32:12.880 --> 01:32:20.880
[Guest]: ek doh poetry meri chhapi Baalhans mein, phir school ke liye, magazine ke liye, I started

01:32:20.880 --> 01:32:25.880
[Guest]: writing, aur school me bhi, class me bhi generally just to show off ki mene yeh seekha hai, ab

01:32:25.880 --> 01:32:31.880
[Guest]: main yeh likhunga aur us tarah ka, and toh woh ek waha se woh chalna shuru hua, toh

01:32:31.880 --> 01:32:38.880
[Guest]: ek taraf kitabe thi, doosri taraf music tha, again my father's influence, unko filme bohot

01:32:38.880 --> 01:32:43.880
[Guest]: pasand hain, toh filmon ke saath saath music ka bohot daada shock hai, humare ghar mein

01:32:43.880 --> 01:32:52.880
[Guest]: kabhi bhi audio cassettes ki kami nahi rahi uss samay, jo bhi naya, kuch bhi classics

01:32:52.880 --> 01:32:59.880
[Guest]: se lekar, the recent TV shows like Mirza Ghalib ka jab audio cassette aaya, so woh jaise

01:32:59.880 --> 01:33:05.880
[Guest]: aaya hoga market mein humare ghar aaya gaya tha, Kabhi Sammilan aur theatre ka bohot daada

01:33:05.880 --> 01:33:10.880
[Guest]: shock tha papa ko, toh hum log woh bhi dekhne jaate the Dehradun mein jahan bhi hota tha,

01:33:10.880 --> 01:33:16.880
[Guest]: and again, so all of these activities kind of created a world for me which was within

01:33:16.880 --> 01:33:23.880
[Guest]: reach, ki theek hai yeh sab aap kar sakte hain, and all of this is a professional whatever

01:33:23.880 --> 01:33:30.880
[Guest]: path you can take, hum theatre, Dehradun mein ek annual theatre festival hota tha, waha

01:33:30.880 --> 01:33:34.880
[Guest]: uss tarah se koi venue nahi tha jaisa Bombay mein yaar Delhi mein hote hain, ki har hafte

01:33:34.880 --> 01:33:40.880
[Guest]: aap dekh sakte hain, but waha ek annual theatre festival hota tha, jo kaafi well funded tha

01:33:40.880 --> 01:33:45.880
[Guest]: it seems, kyuki bade bade theatre groups aate the Delhi se, Bombay se, there were some TV

01:33:45.880 --> 01:33:50.880
[Guest]: actors we had seen from that time, ki Doordarshan mein inka show aata hai, yeh yaah pe perform

01:33:50.880 --> 01:33:56.880
[Guest]: kar rahe hain humare saamne, so woh poora hafta humare liye bohot thrilling hota tha, kyuki

01:33:56.880 --> 01:34:02.880
[Guest]: poora hafte hum log, har roz humko theatre jaane ko milta tha, har roz hum log ek nahi

01:34:02.880 --> 01:34:08.880
[Guest]: kahani dekhte the, lot of these stories were completely not suitable for kids of that age,

01:34:08.880 --> 01:34:16.880
[Guest]: aur suitable hongi bhi toh ya pata nahi, but samajh ke pare thi, like plays like Mahabhoj

01:34:16.880 --> 01:34:22.880
[Guest]: and plays like, which is a very political and very, I would say complicated for a 10

01:34:22.880 --> 01:34:27.880
[Guest]: year old to understand or comprehend ki kya ho raha hai, par uss tarah ke bohot saare,

01:34:27.880 --> 01:34:33.880
[Guest]: ek Teen Tappar naam se play aaya tha, which was again about, I think vaguely I remember

01:34:33.880 --> 01:34:41.880
[Guest]: which was about the fight of a slum, people living in a slum with some, you know, builder

01:34:41.880 --> 01:34:48.880
[Guest]: trying to evacuate them and all, but just the, and that's again, that's the thing with

01:34:48.880 --> 01:34:57.880
[Guest]: art and that's the thing with good art or powerful art, it finds a way to justify itself

01:34:57.880 --> 01:35:02.880
[Guest]: to people, even if you don't understand it, like mujhe kya samajh aaya hoga 8 saal ki

01:35:02.880 --> 01:35:08.880
[Guest]: umar mein jo political kavee samelan ho raha the, wahan pe, haas se kavee samelan ho raha

01:35:08.880 --> 01:35:16.880
[Guest]: the, uss mein kya samajh aaya hoga ki ye jo Rajiv Gandhi pe satire hai, ya LK Advani

01:35:16.880 --> 01:35:24.880
[Guest]: pe satire hai, ya Ram Jethmalani pe satire hai, there was, but there was a poem where

01:35:24.880 --> 01:35:32.880
[Guest]: Rajiv Gandhi is complaining to Indira Gandhi about Ram Jethmalani, teasing him, something

01:35:32.880 --> 01:35:38.880
[Guest]: like that, there was those, ya Vin Chaddha, ye sab naam mene wahan sune jo mujhe kuch

01:35:38.880 --> 01:35:43.880
[Guest]: nahi pata tha, main 9 saal ka, 89 ki baat hai ye, aur ek bahut bada kavee samelan hua

01:35:43.880 --> 01:35:49.880
[Guest]: tha, jismein sab uss samay ke saare jo star kavee the Ashok Chakradhar and Sharad Joshi

01:35:49.880 --> 01:35:56.880
[Guest]: and Surendra Sharma, Hullad Muradabadi, Kaka Hathrasi, Arun Jaimini, lot of these like

01:35:56.880 --> 01:36:08.880
[Guest]: big, big and very political poets of those times and it was the time of VP Singh, Jobi,

01:36:08.880 --> 01:36:17.880
[Guest]: I think VP Singh was the PM at that time when this happened and they're talking about really

01:36:17.880 --> 01:36:24.880
[Guest]: strong political ideas through whatever, through their satire and I was dazzled by it.

01:36:24.880 --> 01:36:29.880
[Guest]: Mujhe aadi cheezein nahi samajh aa rahi hongi, bas tukbandi samajh aa rahi hongi kahin kahin

01:36:29.880 --> 01:36:34.880
[Guest]: ya, kahin kahin koi punchline samajh aa gaye hongi toh aa gaye hongi, but wo itni badi

01:36:34.880 --> 01:36:41.880
[Guest]: cheeze thi Dehradun mein ki uske baad uske cassette, market mein jab aaye, audio cassette,

01:36:41.880 --> 01:36:49.880
[Guest]: wo itne zyada bikhe aur itne mehenge the and still we, my father spent money to buy those

01:36:49.880 --> 01:36:55.880
[Guest]: I think 3 or 4 cassette pack kyuki wo 6 ghante ka program tha total aur wo cassette phir

01:36:55.880 --> 01:36:59.880
[Guest]: hum log baad mein bhot sunte rahe, isliye mujhe bahut saari kavitae uski yaad hain ki

01:36:59.880 --> 01:37:03.880
[Guest]: Sharad Joshi ne kya sunaya tha aur Hullad Muradabadi ne kya sunaya tha.

01:37:03.880 --> 01:37:11.880
[Guest]: Toh waha se yeh doosra influence aaya, kavi sammilan ka, teesra influence aaya poetry

01:37:11.880 --> 01:37:17.880
[Guest]: ka which again mostly because of what Doordarshan was doing at that time with Mirza Ghalib

01:37:17.880 --> 01:37:24.880
[Guest]: aur with Kaikasha kind of shows which was every episode was about one great Urdu poet

01:37:24.880 --> 01:37:31.880
[Guest]: toh usmein koi episode tha jo mere khayal se Mir pe tha, koi episode tha jo Daag Dhelvi

01:37:31.880 --> 01:37:37.880
[Guest]: pe tha, aise alag alag episode, har episode mein ek kisi shayar ki kahani aati thi unka

01:37:37.880 --> 01:37:43.880
[Guest]: almost biopic types, ek hai do episode ka, so uske phir audio cassette aati the, ab

01:37:43.880 --> 01:37:49.880
[Guest]: wo papa sunte the, Mirza Ghalib sunte the, ya Kaikasha sunte the, ya baaki aur Jagjit

01:37:49.880 --> 01:37:52.880
[Guest]: Singh ke bhot saari albums aati the.

01:37:52.880 --> 01:38:02.880
[Guest]: Main wo sunta tha toh mere liye again how art works, music works, no matter you understand

01:38:02.880 --> 01:38:03.880
[Guest]: it or not.

01:38:03.880 --> 01:38:08.880
[Guest]: Ek bhi shabd aapko nahi samajh aa raha hai, theek hai, aapko music toh samajhne ki zaroor

01:38:08.880 --> 01:38:10.880
[Guest]: nahi, aap usmein bhaya jaate hain.

01:38:10.880 --> 01:38:14.880
[Guest]: Jab aap bhaya jaate hain toh phir aap samajhna chahte hain ki achha ismein yeh shabd kya

01:38:14.880 --> 01:38:22.880
[Guest]: hai, toh phir maine thoda pehle sunke samajhna shuru kya ki Mirza Ghalib, jo Jagjit Singh

01:38:22.880 --> 01:38:31.880
[Guest]: ga rahe hain, wo kya ga rahe hain ki, nikalna khuld se aadam ka sunte aaye hain, lekin

01:38:31.880 --> 01:38:36.880
[Guest]: khuld kya hota hai, aadam kya hota hai, bahut beyaabroo hokar tere kooche se hum nikle

01:38:36.880 --> 01:38:40.880
[Guest]: toh beyaabroo kya hota hai, jo sabse aasaan nahi is poore share mein, shayad samajhne

01:38:40.880 --> 01:38:44.880
[Guest]: ki cheez hai, beyaabroo hai, but wo bhi usmein toh nahi pata thi.

01:38:44.880 --> 01:38:49.880
[Guest]: Toh phir dekha ki papa ke book rack mein rakhi hui hai, Mirza Ghalib ka Diwan-e-Ghalib

01:38:49.880 --> 01:38:54.880
[Guest]: ka translation, translation malabhi Hindi jo bhi explanation.

01:38:54.880 --> 01:38:59.880
[Guest]: It was not translation, it was I think Ali Sardar Jafri ki kitab thi, jo ki where he

01:38:59.880 --> 01:39:06.880
[Guest]: kind of writes about each share and gives a bit of context also and all that.

01:39:06.880 --> 01:39:13.880
[Guest]: Toh usmein word meanings bhi the, toh wo kitab utha li, das saal ki umr mein shayad.

01:39:13.880 --> 01:39:18.880
